result.name: Dragon Centre

reviews.text: I love the Dragon Centre. So much variety and great local flair. There is indoor amusement centers and small kiosks and boutiques that are part of the apple mall. You can get relatively cheap massages here...or get a nice set of gel nails. Many choices for eateries here too. The public toilets leave much to the imagination. You can walk here easily from the closets MTR stop.

One of the popular shopping complex in Kowloon west. The target customers are the general public and the younger generations. The top floors are nearly all small shops selling cheap trendy goods aiming the young people. There are many eating outlets and two Chinese Seafood restaurant, which serves good dim sums at off peak hours at a very cheap price.
A great shopping centre with a rustic charm. There's is an unmistakable old vibe to this place; the arcade is a must go to revisit old times.

Very local or kinds of grassroots level commercial centre one may say, where you can buy daily necessary or having a meal there choosing from a variety of restaurants. I always see many western students there, too.
Quite old, unfortunately got there a little late so many shops were shut, I liked the tiny shops at mid levels.
